《'''性本無言'''》（{{lang-uk|'''Плем'я'''}}，{{lang-en|'''The Tribe'''}}）是一部2014年的[[烏克蘭|烏克蘭]][[劇情片|劇情片]]，由{{link-en|米羅斯拉夫·史拉波殊皮斯基|Myroslav Slaboshpytskyi}}編劇並執導，是他的長片處女作。影片以一所聾啞學校為背景，全片只使用烏克蘭[[手語|手語]]而沒有對白，也沒有提供任何字幕、翻譯或旁白。本片入選了[[第67屆康城影展|第67屆康城影展]]{{link-en|國際影評人週單元|International Critics' Week}}，並摘得包括該單元最高獎在內的三項大獎<ref>{{cite web|url=http://variety.com/2014/film/festivals/cannes-slaboshpytskiys-the-tribe-tops-critics-week-1201189254/|title=CANNES: Slaboshpytskiy’s ‘The Tribe’ Tops Critics’ Week|work=《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|綜藝]]》|language=en|accessdate=2015-08-23|date=2014-05-22|archive-date=2016-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809083034/http://variety.com/2014/film/festivals/cannes-slaboshpytskiys-the-tribe-tops-critics-week-1201189254/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==劇情==
在一間寄宿制聾啞學校裡，一羣學生組成了一個犯罪集團，從事搶劫、賣淫等勾當。一位新入學的內向男生謝爾蓋（格雷戈里·費申科飾演）在暴力和威脅的驅使下身不由己地成為了團伙的一份子，並旋即取代了在一次事故中身亡的負責拉皮條的男孩。然而，他很快戀上了賣淫女孩安雅（雅娜·諾維科娃飾演），並決意協助她逃往[[意大利|意大利]]。隨著二人感情的日漸深入和計劃的逐步實行，一場更大的風暴正在醞釀……

==拍攝與上映==
[[File:HKIFF.jpg|thumb]]
影片改編自導演史拉波殊皮斯基曾入圍2010年[[柏林國際影展|柏林國際影展]]的11分鐘短片《Deafness》（{{lang-uk|Глухота}}）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allocine.fr/article/fichearticle_gen_carticle=18634295.html|title=Cannes 2014 - The Tribe : "Baiser, souffrir et mourir, c'est universel"|first=Brigitte|last=Baronnet|work={{link-en|AlloCiné|AlloCiné}}|date=2014-10-01|accessdate=2015-08-23|language=fr|archive-date=2020-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218072316/http://www.allocine.fr/article/fichearticle_gen_carticle=18634295.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。長片的劇本創作工作於2011年完成（因此本片事實上並不如同一些觀眾和評論家認為的那樣，包含對其後[[烏克蘭親歐盟示威運動|烏克蘭政局]]的指涉），拍攝於2013年秋開始<ref>{{cite web|url=http://twitchfilm.com/2015/04/interview-the-tribe-won-37-awards-success-and-corruption-with-myroslav-slaboshpytskiy.html|title=Interview: "THE TRIBE Won 37 Awards" Success And Corruption With Miroslav Slaboshpytskiy|first=Thomas|last=Humphrey|work=Twitch|language=en|accessdate=2015-08-23|date=2015-04-30|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150922050227/http://twitchfilm.com/2015/04/interview-the-tribe-won-37-awards-success-and-corruption-with-myroslav-slaboshpytskiy.html|archivedate=2015-09-22}}</ref><ref name=uaoffice>{{cite web|url=http://filmoffice.org.ua/2013/03/20/in-production/ |title=In Production |work=烏克蘭電影委員會 |date=2013-03-20 |accessdate=2015-08-23 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150923150437/http://filmoffice.org.ua/2013/03/20/in-production/ |archivedate=2015-09-23 }}</ref>。影片拍攝成本約為150萬美元，並在拍攝中得到了烏克蘭國家電影部門的資助<ref name=uaoffice />。

在影片選角期間，有超過300名演員參加了試鏡，所有參與試鏡以及最終參加演出的演員都是聾啞、非專業演員<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/meet-the-2014-afi-filmmakers-8-the-tribe-director-auditioned-over-300-deaf-people-for-his-award-winning-drama-20141111|title=Meet the 2014 AFI Filmmakers #8: 'The Tribe' Director Auditioned Over 300 Deaf People For His Award-Winning Drama|work=[[IndieWire|IndieWire]]|date=2014-11-11|accessdate=2015-08-23|language=en|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304112036/http://www.indiewire.com/article/meet-the-2014-afi-filmmakers-8-the-tribe-director-auditioned-over-300-deaf-people-for-his-award-winning-drama-20141111|dead-url=no}}</ref>。影片中角色交流完全通過烏克蘭手語；儘管導演本人撰寫了劇本，但由於他並不懂手語，因此在現場必須藉助[[手語翻譯|手語翻譯]]以確定演員們的手勢與劇本中的「對白」相符<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/article/how-the-director-of-the-tribe-made-a-movie-in-sign-language-without-speaking-it-20150616|title=How the Director of 'The Tribe' Made a Movie in Sign Language Without Speaking It|work=IndieWire|date=2015-06-16|accessdate=2015-08-23|language=en|first=Eric|last=Kohn|archive-date=2016-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160426160558/http://www.indiewire.com/article/how-the-director-of-the-tribe-made-a-movie-in-sign-language-without-speaking-it-20150616|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

影片於2014年5月21日在第67屆康城影展首映。在進行所有公映和展映時，全手語、無對白的《性本無言》都沒有提供任何字幕、翻譯或旁白等輔助措施以幫助觀眾理解角色間的手語交流。導演史拉波殊皮斯基對此解釋稱：「這樣做的本意就是要讓觀眾在沒有翻譯的情況下看懂電影，也正是觀眾能真正投入欣賞本片的原因之一。」「（在其他電影中，）觀眾必須將精力花費在讀字幕上，而影像的效果就會因此受到損失。這樣看電影太複雜了。」「電影不一定要有對白，所有情感都寫在臉上、表現在動作裡。最重要的東西是人類的情感，而這對於世界上任何一個人來說都是清晰易懂的。」<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/how-sign-language-thriller-the-tribe-became-2015-s-most-intense-film-20150615|title=How Sign-Language Thriller 'The Tribe' Became 2015's Most Intense Film|work=《[[滾石_(雜誌)|滾石]]》|language=en|date=2015-06-15|accessdate=2015-08-23|first=Jason|last=Newman|quote=The concept was that people must understand it without the translation. [...] It's one of the reasons why the audience is deeply involved in the story. [In other movies], you must always pay attention to the subtitles and you lose something from the image. It’s a very complicated way to watch a film. [...] It isn't a necessity to have dialogue in film — everything is written on a face and all is visible in the movements. The main thing is human emotion — that's clear and understandable to any person in the world.|archive-date=2017-11-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171122012238/http://www.rollingstone.com/movies/news/how-sign-language-thriller-the-tribe-became-2015-s-most-intense-film-20150615|dead-url=no}}</ref>

